AN 18-year-old man has been arrested and charged in connection with the attempted murder of a Chinese takeaway owner. Man on murder bid charge AN 18-year-old man has been arrested and charged in connection with the attempted murder of a Chinese takeaway owner.Police are treating the incident, which took place in West Pilton Park, Edinburgh, at 9.35pm on Wednesday, as a hate crime.The 37-year-old victim, named as dad-of-three Jie Yu, suffered multiple injuries in the attack.